  "text": ", and A3AR À/À [CITATION_1] , mice to renal IP prior to ischemia. For this purpose, mice were subjected to 45 min of renal artery occlusion with or without prior IP (four cycles, 4 min ischemia, 4 min reperfusion) followed by 24 h of reperfusion until assessment of renal function. To avoid surgical trauma during the procedure, we utilized a recently described model of intermittent renal artery occlusion via a hanging-weight system for isolated renal artery occlusion [CITATION_2] .",
